- The timing mini-game uses a bouncing cursor (reflect off 0 and 1): `p = 2 - p` when overshooting 1, `p = -p` when going below 0. This handles arbitrary large `dt` correctly without loops (since max single-frame overshoot is bounded by frame rate).
- `selectFishSpecies` uses cumulative weight subtraction rather than building a CDF array вҖ” O(n) with no allocations per call.
- Seasonal weights are sparse вҖ” missing species default to 1.0 via `?? 1.0`, making the config concise without needing to enumerate every species Г— season pair.
